Import Metabolites and Metadata¶

Metabolite data is imported from two different files:

metabolites: includes measurments for metabolites that were present in at least 75 % of the individuals in the dataset and are expressed as continuous variables

metabolites_binary: includes measurements for metabolites that were present in at least 25 %, but fewer than 75 % of the individuals in the dataset

Logistic regression¶

Logistic regression models are used to find associations between metabolites and autism. Three different models (per metabolite) are used:

Model 1: Autism ~ Metabolite + season of birth + age at sampling + year of birth

Model 2: Autism ~ Metabolite + season of birth + age at sampling + year of birth + family history of psychiatric disorders

Model 3: Autism ~ Metabolite + season of birth + age at sampling + year of birth + family history of psychiatric disorders + genetic risk score for autism + Principal component 1-6

In [27]:
output_logreg <- cbind.data.frame(names(X))
colnames(output_logreg)[1] <- "Metabolite"
output_logreg["OR_logreg"]  <- sapply(1:length(a),function(n){exp(coef(summary(logreg[[n]]))[2,1])})
output_logreg["logOR_logreg"]  <- sapply(1:length(a),function(n){coef(summary(logreg[[n]]))[2,1]})
output_logreg["p_logreg"] <- sapply(1:length(a),function(n){coef(summary(logreg[[n]]))[2,4]})
output_logreg["CI_low_logreg"] <- sapply(1:length(a),function(n){exp(confint.default(logreg[[n]]))[2]})
output_logreg["CI_high_logreg"] <- sapply(1:length(a),function(n){exp(confint.default(logreg[[n]])[12])})
output_logreg["p_fdr_logreg"] <- p.adjust(output_logreg$p_logreg,method="fdr")
output_logreg["p_bonf_logreg"] <- p.adjust(output_logreg$p_logreg,method="bonferroni")
output_logreg["significant_logreg"] <- ifelse(output_logreg$p_fdr<0.05,"Significant","Nonsignificant")
output_logreg <- merge(output_logreg,annotations,by.x="Metabolite",by.y="id",all.x=TRUE)
output_logreg["significant_nominal"] <- ifelse(output_logreg$p_logreg>0.05,"Nonsignificant",
                                               ifelse(output_logreg$p_fdr_logreg<0.05,"Significant",
                                                      "Nominally significant"))

Stratify on time-to-disease¶
